OpenGraph

public OpenGraph(java.lang.String url,
                 boolean ignoreSpecErrors)
          throws java.io.IOException,
                 java.lang.Exception
Fetch the open graph representation from a web site

Parameters:
url - The address to the web page to fetch Open Graph data
ignoreSpecErrors - Set this option to true if you don't wish to have an exception throw if the page does not conform to the basic 4 attributes
Throws:
java.io.IOException - If a network error occurs, the HTML parser will throw an IO Exception
java.lang.Exception - A generic exception is throw if the specific page fails to conform to the basic Open Graph standard as define by the constant REQUIRED_META
